":0,"dislike":14,"score":-14,"quote":{"pid":"0d575fefd140ea20dea390318e237bb1aacbcf97","tid":2231854,"uid":41308,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-10-06T03:56:25.000Z","msg":"陳同佳呢條MK仔幾時會去台灣槍斃？<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":4,"replyTime":"2020-10-06T04:05:49.000Z","msg":"At the TaiWan when are the this MK son(Chan Tung gai)can execute by shoot？"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-10-06T13:59:13.000Z","msg":"陳同佳呢條MK仔<span class=\"red\">幾時會</span>去台灣槍斃<br />\n<br />\n<span class=\"red\">When will</span> the MK kid called Tung Gai Chan go to Taiwan and be executed by shooting? <br />\n<br />\n或者<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n1. 英文姓氏放最後<br />\n<br />\n2.「幾時會」因為未發生，所以係用 future tense 「when will」。 <br />\n<br />\n用present tense 嘅話：<br />\nWhen is ... going to Taiwan and be executed by shooting.<br />\n<br />\n但呢句句子暗示你已知陳同佳會去台灣槍斃，單純唔知確實時間。<br />\n<br />\n3. 因為Subject 係人名，所以就算用present tense 都會係when is 而唔係when are (眾數，或者subject 係you)<br />\n<br />\n4. 因為用future tense, 所以成句會係 when will S+V+O<br />\n但如果你係用present tense, when are/is 嘅 (are/is) 已經係動詞，所以要<br />\na, modify 做 when are/is S going to V+O<br />\nb, modify 做 when are/is 名詞<br />\nc, modify 做 when do/does S+V<br />\n<br />\n例句： <br />\na, When is 陳同佳 going to be executed by shooting (問已知會發生，但你唔確定日期嘅事）<br />\nb, When is 陳同佳's execution day (問日期，節日）<br />\nc, when does the store open (問一啲恆常發生嘅事）<br />\n<br />\n如果要用can, 就會係 when can S+V+O. 唔會when are/is/do 再加個can 喺後面<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n5, Taiwan 當一字<br />\n<br />\n6, 仔譯kid, son 係解兒子，同時可以解細路（美）。但如果用son 講細路嘅話，通常都係正面對話嘅時候，年長者對年幼者講，同埋唔會同其他字合埋。 e.g. &quot;Don't fuck with me, son.&quot; <br />\n所以用boy/kid 會合理啲。<br />\n<br />\n7, 槍斃係叫execution by shooting"},{"pid":"3c19ab5ae94f9baf836102ca47fd21757a72cc08","tid":2231854,"uid":296431,"like":4,"dislike":0,"score":4,"quote":{"pid":"7326d0b6128f2230df5e8cf2d497a41587ea7885","tid":2231854,"uid":219583,"like":33,"dislike":1,"score":32,"cited